5: All clear. You can come on out.
9:
It's kinda anti-climactic how easy this
is. You sure know your stuff, Marianne.
12:
Hah. I may not be the best maid, but I 
know how to command an infiltration 
party.
17:
Why'd we lure that guy over? Couldn't
you just shoot him?
21: I'd prefer not to... Too loud.
24:
Let's get moving. We have to strike 
before they catch on to us.
28:
Bout time you showed up! You'll pay 
for what you did to us!
31:
I'll give you one chance to surrender. 
Step away from her, or I'll shoot.
34:
Surrender? When I've got the upper 
hand?
36:
Get down and beg for forgiveness, or 
the girl gets it!
39:
She's an innocent civilian! How DARE 
you?!
41:
Playin' by the rules doesn't win you 
any wars, kid. I found that monster's 
weakness, and I'm damn well gonna 
exploit it! *spits* Shoot if you dare!
46: It's okay. I believe in you.
47:
Yo-you're out of your mind! She's a 
coldblooded bastard, but even SHE 
wouldn't shoot through a hostage!
50:
Last warning. *click* 
Surrender, or I shoot.
60:
There. Cleaned the place out.
...You're next.
66:
Ye-yeah. I knew you'd come to save 
me!
69:
I'm glad you're unharmed. *sigh* 
I guess this is farewell.
76:
Hang on, Marianne. We've still got 
that performance review, right? Let's 
slow down and talk things over.
79:
Yeah! She's important to you, right? 
Are you REALLY just gonna leave her 
high and dry without explaining 
anything?
83:
What's there to explain? I'm not cut 
out to live a normal, peaceful life.
86:
Whenever I'm with you, I get so scared
I'm doing everything wrong, but when 
I pulled that trigger, I felt... relief.
88:
The time I spent with you felt like a 
dream, but now it's time I woke up. 
I tried to be a maid—your Marianne—
but I failed. I'm sorry.
95:
Of course you'd feel more confident 
doing something you've done for 
years! So what?! I didn't learn to be 
a maid overnight either!
96:
I KNOW you used to be a soldier. 
I know, but... *hic* I'M the one who told 
you to pull the trigger. I told you, 
I believe in you. No matter what!
97:
A-and I've told you a million times, if 
you EVER need help, you have me, so... 
Don't be scared.
100:
Haha, you're not winning this fight, 
Marianne.
107:
You wouldn't make it on the battlefield
anymore. She's softened you up too 
much.
109: Think about what you want to do.
116:
Well, I know I DON'T want to hold you 
back.
119:
You're always helping me, so I... I want 
to be the kind of person you can rely 
on when YOU need help!
121:
S-so I... want to stay with you. Side by 
side, helping each other.
...Do you mind?
128:
All's well that ends well. You've both 
had a long day—it's time we all 
headed back and got some rest.
132:
Yeah, maids have to be up early, after 
all. I've still got work to do as your 
housekeeper, right, Milord? I'm looking 
forward to it.
